{"article_id":"Ijv02yfrCmxfze2j","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The White House says","depth":8},{"id":1,"text":"it is `` extremely disappointed '' in Russia 's decision","depth":9},{"id":2,"text":"to grant a temporary one-year asylum to NSA leaker Edward Snowden .","depth":9},{"id":3,"text":"Snowden left Moscow 's Sheremetyevo Airport on Thursday","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"after spending more than a month holed up in its transit center .","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"Anatoly Kucherena , a Russian lawyer","depth":9},{"id":6,"text":"who has been advising the former U.S. intelligence contractor ,","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"told Russian media","depth":8},{"id":8,"text":"that Snowden 's whereabouts are being kept secret for security reasons .","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"`` We are extremely disappointed","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"that the Russian government would take this step","depth":10},{"id":11,"text":"despite our clear lawful requests in public and private","depth":12},{"id":12,"text":"to have Mr. Snowden expelled to the U.S.","depth":13},{"id":13,"text":"to face the charges against him , ''","depth":13},{"id":14,"text":"White House Press Secretary Jay Carney says .","depth":11},{"id":15,"text":"`` Mr. Snowden is not a whistleblower .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"He 's accused of leaking classified information ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"charged with felony counts ,","depth":11},{"id":18,"text":"and should be returned to the U.S. as soon as possible ,","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"where he 'll be accorded due process . ''","depth":12},{"id":20,"text":"NPR 's Ari Shapiro forwarded us those notes from Carney 's daily news briefing with reporters .","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"`` This move by the Russian government undermines a long history of cooperation with Russia ,","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"''","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"Carney says ,","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"`` cooperation","depth":8},{"id":25,"text":"that 's been on the upswing since the Boston bombings . ''","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"President Obama is scheduled to visit Russia in September","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"to attend the G-20 economic summit .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"Those meetings will be held St. Petersburg ;","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"even before Thursday 's events , tension between the U.S. and Russia over Snowden had fueled speculation","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that Obama might not visit Russian President Vladimir Putin in Moscow during his trip .","depth":11},{"id":31,"text":"Carney says","depth":10},{"id":32,"text":"that in light of what he said is `` not a positive development , '' the White House is `` evaluating the utility of a summit . ''","depth":10},{"id":33,"text":"When asked what steps the United States might take","depth":10},{"id":34,"text":"now that Snowden has been given asylum ,","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"Carney said ,","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"`` We 'll obviously be in contact with Russian authorities","depth":11},{"id":37,"text":"expressing our extreme disappointment in this decision ''","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"and reiterating the case","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"to return the former intelligence contract employee to the U.S .","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"Speaking earlier this summer about Snowden 's search for a safe haven","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"as U.S. authorities pursue espionage charges against him ,","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"Russian President Vladimir Putin said","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"Snowden could stay in Russia","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"only if he stops any activities","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"that would damage the United States ,","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"NPR 's Corey Flintoff reminds us .","depth":9},{"id":47,"text":"`` Britain 's Guardian newspaper has published new information about U.S. programs , ''","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Corey says ,","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"`` and is said to have much more information","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"that Snowden provided . ''","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"On Wednesday , the newspaper published information on a program called XKeyscore ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"which it compared to the previously disclosed PRISM .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"The Guardian reported","depth":12},{"id":54,"text":"that XKeyscore allows NSA analysts to `` mine enormous agency databases '' with only a cursory explanation .","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"The Guardian suggested","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"that the program could give an analyst access to `` nearly everything","depth":14},{"id":57,"text":"a typical user does on the Internet ''","depth":14},{"id":58,"text":"- including Americans and foreigners ,","depth":14},{"id":59,"text":"as The Two-Way reported Wednesday .","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"It 's not yet clear whether Snowden pledged to stop the flow of secret information","depth":7},{"id":61,"text":"in order to receive asylum .","depth":7},{"id":62,"text":"In the past , Putin has suggested","depth":7},{"id":63,"text":"the complicated Snowden case may be more trouble","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"than it 's worth .","depth":8},{"id":65,"text":"Or at least , that 's what we were left to believe","depth":8},{"id":66,"text":"after he unveiled this simile in June :","depth":8},{"id":67,"text":"`` In any case , I would like not to deal with such issues","depth":8},{"id":68,"text":"because it is like shearing a pig :","depth":9},{"id":69,"text":"There 's lots of squealing and little fleece . ''","depth":9},{"id":70,"text":"Update at 8:35 a.m . ET :","depth":6},{"id":71,"text":"WikiLeaks Reacts To Snowden 's Departure","depth":6},{"id":72,"text":"`` We would like to thank the Russian people and all those others","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"who have helped to protect Mr. Snowden , ''","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"WikiLeaks says .","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"`` We have won the battle","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"-- now the war . ''","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"The anti-secrecy group ,","depth":9},{"id":78,"text":"which has been in contact with Snowden","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"since he was in Hong Kong ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"says","depth":8},{"id":81,"text":"that the American `` has now left Moscow airport under the care of WikiLeaks ' Sarah Harrison . ''","depth":7},{"id":82,"text":"News of Snowden 's departure from Sheremetyevo International Airport comes","depth":5},{"id":83,"text":"one day after his father , Lon , told The Washington Post","depth":8},{"id":84,"text":"that he had declined an offer","depth":9},{"id":85,"text":"to travel to Moscow in an effort","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"to get his son to come back to the United States .","depth":10},{"id":87,"text":"Lon Snowden said","depth":10},{"id":88,"text":"the proposal fell apart","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"after FBI officials said","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"they could not guarantee","depth":11},{"id":91,"text":"he would speak with his son .","depth":11},{"id":92,"text":"`` I said ,","depth":10},{"id":93,"text":"'Wait a minute , folks ,","depth":11},{"id":94,"text":"I 'm not going to sit on the tarmac","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"to be an emotional tool for you , ' ``","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"Snowden told The Post 's Jerry Markon .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"Edward Snowden , 30 , faces charges of espionage","depth":8},{"id":98,"text":"for releasing classified documents to The Guardian and other news media","depth":9},{"id":99,"text":"detailing the National Security Agency 's broad spying programs and , in particular , its ability","depth":10},{"id":100,"text":"to monitor the phone and Internet activity of American citizens .","depth":10},{"id":101,"text":"In his interview with The Post , Lon Snowden said","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"his son loves the United States","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"and grew up around law enforcement officials in Maryland .","depth":10},{"id":104,"text":"He also said ,","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"`` If he comes back to the United States ,","depth":10},{"id":106,"text":"he is going to be treated horribly .","depth":11},{"id":107,"text":"He is going to be thrown into a hole .","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"He is not going to be allowed to speak . ''","depth":12},{"id":109,"text":"Since the revelations about the NSA 's spying abilities , the U.S. government has attempted to reassure Americans","depth":4},{"id":110,"text":"that their privacy is not at risk .","depth":4},{"id":111,"text":"Several hearings in Congress have focused on the matter ,","depth":4},{"id":112,"text":"and","depth":6},{"id":113,"text":"as The Two-Way reported yesterday ,","depth":7},{"id":114,"text":"NSA director Gen. Keith Alexander told a crowd at a large annual hackers ' convention in Las Vegas","depth":8},{"id":115,"text":"that the agency 's analysts do not abuse their authority .","depth":8},{"id":116,"text":"And","depth":6},{"id":117,"text":"`` if they did , ''","depth":8},{"id":118,"text":"he said ,","depth":8},{"id":119,"text":"`` our auditing tools would detect them","depth":8},{"id":120,"text":"and they would be held accountable . ''","depth":8},{"id":121,"text":"NSA leaker Edward Snowden has left Moscow 's airport ,","depth":6},{"id":122,"text":"his Russian legal adviser told reporters Thursday .","depth":6},{"id":123,"text":"Snowden arrived at Moscow 's Sheremetyevo Airport from Hong Kong more than a month ago ,","depth":6},{"id":124,"text":"after news media published a trove of secret U.S. documents","depth":7},{"id":125,"text":"supplied by the former National Security Agency contractor .","depth":7},{"id":126,"text":"The White House is `` extremely disappointed '' by the action ,","depth":6},{"id":127,"text":"says Press Secretary Jay Carney .","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"Snowden 's Russian adviser , Anatoly Kucherena , `` has told reporters","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"that he passed along documents to Edward Snowden","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"allowing him to enter Russian soil , ''","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"NPR 's Corey Flintoff reports from Moscow .","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"`` Kucherena and sources at Sheremetyevo Airport say","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"Snowden has left the airport . ''","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"Snowden has been granted asylum for a period of at least one year .","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"Earlier Thursday , WikiLeaks tweeted ,","depth":4},{"id":136,"text":"`` Edward Snowden has successfully acquired refugee status in Russia","depth":5},{"id":137,"text":"and will shortly leave the airport . ''","depth":5},{"id":138,"text":"We will update this post with more details","depth":3},{"id":139,"text":"as they emerge .","depth":3}],"relations":[{"parent":279,"left":260,"right":278,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":260,"left":248,"right":259,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":248,"left":209,"right":247,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":165,"right":208,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":148,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":144,"right":147,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":144,"left":142,"right":143,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":0,"right":141,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":141,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":146,"right":8,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":146,"left":145,"right":7,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":145,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":159,"right":163,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":158,"right":20,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":153,"right":157,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":9,"right":152,"relation":"attribution","nuclear